<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<caldef:CalDefinitionFile xmlns:caldef="http://www.caltools.gm.com/caldef" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" CalDefCategory="Audio" Description="This file contains caldefs for the dynamic distortion limiting defined in GIS-604.">
  <CalDefFileVersion>7</CalDefFileVersion>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>1</Version>
    <Date>20JAN2014</Date>
    <Description>Initial release as part of GIS-604 V1.1 finalization.</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>02SEPT2014</Date>
    <Description>Added missing calibrations from GIS-604-240 such as DDL Enabled, FrontRearLimiterCombined, and LOUDNESS_OFFSET.</Description>
    <Author>Dominic Colella</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <Date>29SEP14</Date>
    <Description>Add Usage on all components</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <Date>4/17/2015</Date>
    <Description>Per request from Sanghyun Ryu updated AmplifierHardwareClipSignalType cal in this caldef file to remove usage of Low Radio.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>5</Version>
    <Date>6/14/2017</Date>
    <Description>Updated the usage field for all of the calibration in this caldef file to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>6</Version>
    <Date>9/30/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the DistortionLimiting.caldef file, added GEM usage to the following calibrations within this caldef: (1.) DDL_ENABLE (2. ) FrontSoftwareClipDetectorThreshold, (3.) FrontSoftwareClipDetectorAttackTime, (4.) FrontSoftwareClipDetectorReleaseTime, (5.) FrontLimiterMinimumGain, (6.) FrontLimiterAttackRate, (7.) FrontLimiterReleaseRate, (8.) FrontClipSignalSelection, (8.) RearSoftwareClipDetectorThreshold, (9.)  RearSoftwareClipDetectorAttackTime, (10.) BT_IN_BAND_RINGING, (11.) RearSoftwareClipDetectorReleaseTime, (12.) RearLimiterMinimumGain, (13.) RearLimiterAttackRate, (14.) RearLimiterReleaseRate, (15.) RearClipSignalSelection, (16.) FrontRearLimiterCombination, (17.) LOUDNESS_OFFSET, and (18.) LOUDNESS_COMP_ENABLE. Since these calibrations fell within the current criteria of requiring GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>7</Version>
    <Date>27MAR2019</Date>
    <Description>Added 'ENTRY_VCU' and 'VCU' tags for initial creation of VCS compatible CalDefDatabase for version GIS-646 V6.0.0 release.</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefinition Description="All amplifier outputs including both the CSM and Low Radio’s internal amplifiers as well as those in a remote amplifier shall provide some form of Dynamic Distortion Limiting to minimize or eliminate clipping of the amplifier speaker output and minimize speaker distortions- The distortion limiting algorithm shall include the following capabilities:  1.&#x9;The DDL algorithm shall be applied to all amplified speaker outputs.  2.&#x9;It should be possible, to enable / disable the DDL. " Name="DDL_ENABLE" References="GIS-604-240 Dynamic Distortion Limiting (DDL)" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
    <CalID>_eQ3R4DLREeSm0acW-cA1AQ</CalID>
    <Type>Boolean</Type>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>9/30/2017</Date>
      <Description>Updated the usage field for this calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Boolean>
      <Value>true</Value>
    </Boolean>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="Defines the behavior of the amplifier hardware clip signal for a specific vehicle. " Name="AmplifierHardwareClipSignalType" References="GIS-604-240" Usage="MID,HIGH,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,VCU">
    <CalID>_d3vEUHxzEeOvGYtg-Dwcrw</CalID>
    <Type>Enumeration</Type>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>4/17/2015</Date>
      <Description>Per request from Sanghyun Ryu updated AmplifierHardwareClipSignalType cal to remove usage of Low Radio.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Enumeration>
      <EnumID>__drVoHxyEeOvGYtg-Dwcrw</EnumID>
      <Value>0</Value>
    </Enumeration>
  </CalDefinition>
